in {{state_view.py}}:
{code}
    merkle_db = MerkleDatabase(self._database)
    if state_root_hash is not None:
        merkle_db.set_merkle_root(state_root_hash)
{code}

in {{merkle.py}}:
{code}
def __init__(self, database, merkle_root=INIT_ROOT_KEY):
        self._database = database
        self.set_merkle_root(merkle_root)
{code}

The call to {{set_merkle_root}} does a db put when the {{INIT_ROOT_KEY}} is the root. So, every instance of {{StateView}} is incurring the cost of a db write.

