The way the block info currently validates timestamps will cause a validator who is trying to catch up on blocks to fail if it is catching up too far in the future.

In particular, inside sawtooth-core/families/block_info/sawtooth_block_info/processor/handler.py in the method validate_timestamp, the check
{code}
if abs(now - timestamp) > tolerance
{code}
should probably be something like
{code}
if time.time() + tolerance < timestamp:
{code}

