{{" signer_public_key:\\"021b4bc864eba3ed5cebbfd6ec336f13b2c0bb34cda48e254ae9f31e236f8cd8c9}}
{{" " header_signature:"fed61d8ce9c9b7a1d77919fc262eadeafe23027286fe01abfca0c92a36900db3" payload:"dGVzdGluZ19uZXcsY3JlYXRlLA==" > > '}}

When used in constructors, the value of "msg.sender" is the address of the contract account, instead of the external account creating the contract. This behavior is different from Ethereum.

For the following contract:

contract MyToken \{
    address owner;

    function MyToken() public \{
        owner = msg.sender;
    }

    function isOwned() public constant returns (bool b) \{
        return owner == msg.sender;
    }

    function getOwner() public constant returns (address a) \{
        return owner;
    }
}

When created with "seth contract create" and called with "seth contract call", isOwned() will return false, and "owner" holds the address of the contract account instead of the user's account.

