When the sw developer select to continue with already involved GPB (Google ProtoBuffers) please consider this situation:
{noformat}
message Doom { 
   enum Action { 
      FATALITY = 0; 
      NOTHING_IMPORTANT = 1; 
      BLABLA = 2; 
      LAST_ONE = 3;  
  } 
   Action action = 1; 
   string devastating_structure = 2; 
}
{noformat}
Key features of the GPB's:
 * all properties are optional
 * enum *must* start from 0

when the devastating_structure is not filled and the action is *FATALITY* the hard crash of the application is served on the table with the sweet text *Segmentation fault*.

